00:33:27.120 --> 00:33:30.000
And what better way to tell
a story about a comic book

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:34.330
application than doing a comic?

00:33:34.610 --> 00:33:37.410
So this all started with a colleague
of mine calling me and saying,

00:33:37.440 --> 00:33:39.100
"Erik,
you've got to check out this application.

00:33:39.100 --> 00:33:39.570
It's great.

00:33:39.650 --> 00:33:40.440
My kids love it.

00:33:40.500 --> 00:33:41.400
Your kids would love it.

00:33:41.530 --> 00:33:45.780
You can make comic books."
So I downloaded it,

00:33:45.780 --> 00:33:47.340
took a look at it.

00:33:47.510 --> 00:33:49.250
It's a beautiful Cocoa UI.

00:33:49.250 --> 00:33:53.490
One of the things that we really look for
is how are you leveraging the platform?

00:33:53.500 --> 00:33:56.000
You've heard a lot about
that at the conference.

00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:58.270
What are you doing with our tools?

00:33:58.440 --> 00:34:00.500
How are you paying attention
to the user experience,

00:34:00.500 --> 00:34:01.100
et cetera?

00:34:01.100 --> 00:34:03.100
And this was one of those
apps that really grabs you.

00:34:03.100 --> 00:34:04.020
It's intuitive.

00:34:04.020 --> 00:34:04.990
It's beautiful.

00:34:04.990 --> 00:34:05.700
It's fun.

00:34:05.700 --> 00:34:06.900
It's whimsical.

00:34:06.920 --> 00:34:07.890
They did a great job.

00:34:08.020 --> 00:34:09.660
So I thought,
I'm going to get on the phone,

00:34:09.700 --> 00:34:11.120
and I'm going to call these guys.

00:34:11.200 --> 00:34:12.600
I've never heard of them.

00:34:12.600 --> 00:34:13.240
Who are they?

00:34:13.400 --> 00:34:15.710
They're doing great stuff.

00:34:15.810 --> 00:34:20.070
And I ended up talking to the gentleman
who's up on the upper left-hand side,

00:34:20.150 --> 00:34:24.940
Robert Grant, and he gives me a little
description about this company.

00:34:25.050 --> 00:34:29.970
Three guys, one in South Carolina,
one in Switzerland, one in Melbourne,

00:34:29.970 --> 00:34:32.430
Australia,
and they collaborate online and

00:34:32.430 --> 00:34:34.770
build this great application.

00:34:35.180 --> 00:34:37.220
Well, they've grown a little bit
more than the three now,

00:34:37.220 --> 00:34:38.990
so they're doing well.

00:34:40.670 --> 00:34:41.920
And they start telling me the story.

00:34:41.920 --> 00:34:44.490
Well, first of all, they're, of course,
